parameters: \gnrHere is the second floor. I'll inform the
king that you four have arrived. Follow the
carpet and take the next flight of stairs
\knightThis is not good news at all... has
the general given us a new plan yet?
\p2Not to snoop, but... isn't that the king and Oriel?
\oriDon't you understand? That seal wasn't put there
to keep out idiots like that gaggle of cretins
you sent on a suicide mission. It was put there
for the sole purpose of keeping \c[18]Apocalypse\c[0] OUT!
\oriYou've already seen the chaos \c[18]he\c[0]'s caused in the
past decade, and that was merely a fraction of \c[18]his\c[0]
power leaking through the seal. Now that \c[18]he\c[0]'s escaped,
\c[18]he\c[0]'ll finally be able to reach \c[18]his\c[0] full power.
\oriThe Great Collapse... it's beginning once more.
\oriWell, what are you waiting for? If you're listening
in on us, at least make yourselves comfortable.
\oriIf you couldn't tell already, things are BAD.
Once-empty caves and fields are suddenly being
flooded with monsters, and troops on patrol are
being ambushed and killed without warning.
\ori\c[18]Apocalypse\c[0] has broken free from his prison,
and \c[18]he\c[0]'s more than ready to exact revenge.
\p2Do we even know where he went? Last time we
saw him, he jumped into some weird portal.
\oriPart of the problem is we're missing that
information. Though now that you mention it,
I might know a way I can track him down...
\oriThere's a large amount of magical interference...
somehow more than when \c[18]he\c[0] was just under us.
\oriIf I'm ever going to be able to track him down,
the world's going to have to get a lot more pure.
\kingI know you're very against my employment of
the champions, Oriel, but please... at least
these four. You know they're a level above the
others. You can count on them.
\oriIf you're still set on that, we have nothing more to
speak about. I'll be off making another plan for you.
\kingAnd that's that. The general has all the
information you need. Good luck out there!
\p4Not so fast... you know we still have
\p4You can't just lock us in a dungeon with \c[18]Apocalypse\c[0]
himself and expect us to be ok with that. What were
you actually thinking? That was absolutely insane.
\kingHonestly, it was a last minute decision. Oriel
had been bugging me about the seal for a long time,
but the importance of keeping \c[18]Apocalypse\c[0] locked in
had just dawned on me at the time.
\kingSo many plans had been set in motion already, and
I figured none of you would agree to being locked
in... so I had to make it a surprise.
\kingI unlocked the door after hearing the cries of the
injured champions, but \c[18]Apocalypse\c[0] must have used his
magic to sense an escape route. I'm terribly sorry,
I locked you all in and I didn't even follow through...
\p4You can't do stuff like that. If we're going
to work together to keep saving the world,
you can't break our trust like that.
\kingI figure you don't want to talk to me anymore.
